# Codomyrmex workspace

## First reads

- Root `CLAUDE.md` — `uv sync`, `uv run pytest`, architecture, Cursor/MCP notes.
- Root `AGENTS.md` — surfaces and module navigation.
- Root `SPEC.md` — scope when requirements are unclear.

## Tooling

- Python: **`uv run`** for all commands; dependencies in `pyproject.toml` (no `pip install` for project deps).
- **Zero-mock tests** — real implementations, `skipif` for external-only cases.

## Extra rule sources

- `cursorrules/general.cursorrules` — full project-wide policy text.
- `cursorrules/codomyrmex-cursor.cursorrules` — Codomyrmex ↔ Cursor checklist (duplicate of key points).

## Codomyrmex MCP (when the bridge is enabled)

- `codomyrmex.ide_cursor_workspace_info`
- `codomyrmex.ide_cursor_get_active_file`
- `codomyrmex.ide_cursor_rules_read`

If the MCP server cwd is not this repo root, set **`CODOMYRMEX_CURSOR_WORKSPACE`** to the repository path.

Details: `docs/development/cursor-integration.md`, `src/codomyrmex/ide/MCP_TOOL_SPECIFICATION.md`.

## RASP per directory

Where you work, keep `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `SPEC.md`, `PAI.md` aligned with code.
